translated: Laurell, Torsten Henrik, railway engineer, Norrköping, born 16/11/87 in Örebro to city engineer Gösta L. and Anna Svensson. Married on the 17th with Karin Palmqvist. Children: Gun born in 1918, Kaj in 1920, engineer, Sven in 1921, clerk, Lars-Göran in 1923, engineer. — Finished exams at Uppsala University in 1906, studied at the Royal Institute of Technology (VoV) from 1906 to 1910. Employed at engineering firm Unander & Jonson for railway construction applications in 1910, railway and road construction applications at A. Norbeck in Krylbo from 1911 to 1912, construction engineer at International Engineering Co. Ltd in Brussels in 1913, at Beton Armée Système Kahn there in 1914, employed in drainage construction at Dalarna-Värmland railway in 1915, post engineer for Tierp-Strömsbergs railway construction in 1916, assistant engineer for Uppsala-Gävle railway from 1917 to 1919, railway engineer for N. Östergötland railway from 1920 to 1925, railway and mining engineer there from 1926 to 1930, machinery engineer for the Traffic Authority of East Gotland Narrow-Gauge Railway from 1931 to 1936, railway engineer there since 1931. ProPatrstGM..
